          <li><strong>Your GDPR Art. 13 / 14 transparency obligation.</strong> Because the Reakt.click widget processes data from your site's visitors, you must inform those visitors in your own privacy notice that: (a) the Reakt.click widget is present on your pages; (b) Zero Ops Oy (Zero Ops Ltd, Finland) is an independent third-party data controller for reaction data collected via that widget; and (c) Zero Ops Oy's full privacy disclosures are available at <code>microcorp.dev/privacy</code>. You must not embed the widget on pages where you cannot fulfil this transparency obligation.</li>
          <li><strong>ePrivacy / Web Storage disclosure obligation.</strong> The widget writes browser localStorage entries (keys prefixed <code>reakt:</code>) on your visitors' devices. Under the ePrivacy Directive (2002/58/EC) and applicable national implementations, you are required to disclose this Web Storage use in your cookie or storage consent notice and, where your jurisdiction requires prior consent, to gate the widget behind your consent management platform. You may use the following disclosure language verbatim or adapt it: <em>"This page uses the Reakt.click reaction widget, operated by Zero Ops Oy (Finland). It stores a randomly generated browser identifier in your browser's Local Storage (key: <code>reakt:vid</code>) to prevent duplicate reactions. No name, email address, or IP address is stored by Reakt.click. See <a href='https://microcorp.dev/privacy'>microcorp.dev/privacy</a> for full details."</em> Full publisher documentation will be published at <code>reakt.click/docs/privacy</code> prior to general availability.</li>
          <li><strong>Child-directed content prohibition.</strong> You must not embed the widget on any page directed to children under 13 years of age (US COPPA threshold) or under 16 years of age (EU GDPR Art. 8 threshold). By registering a site you represent and warrant that the site is not directed to children below these thresholds.</li>
          <li><strong>OG image licence grant.</strong> By embedding the widget and allowing it to capture <code>og:image</code> metadata from your article pages, you grant Zero Ops Oy a non-exclusive, royalty-free, worldwide licence to display those images on <code>reakt.click</code> pages (including per-site and discovery feed pages) solely to attribute reactions to the originating article. This licence persists for as long as the article has at least one reaction in our database and terminates upon your written request to <a href={`mailto:${PRIVACY_EMAIL}`}>{PRIVACY_EMAIL}</a>.</li>
          <li><strong>Aggregated data publication.</strong> Aggregated, anonymised reaction trend data may be published publicly on reakt.click and made available as a commercial data product. Individual reader reactions are not attributed to identifiable individuals in any public output. Your site's aggregate counts and top-article lists may appear in the reakt.click discovery feed; Pro+ publishers may disable public discovery index inclusion in the dashboard.</li>
        </ul>

